}

export const Radius = {
  sm: 8, md: 12, lg: 16, xl: 20, pill: 100,
}
```

---

## Copy Rules

These strings must appear exactly as specified. Store in `/constants/copy.ts`.

Never use: "failed", "broke your streak", "you missed", "back to zero", "lost"

Always use variants of: "keep going", "a small step counts", "protect your momentum", "try the tiny version", "today is a good day to restart"

---

## Component Rules

- Every component gets its own file in `/components`
- Props must be fully typed with TypeScript interfaces
- No inline anonymous functions in JSX for performance-sensitive lists (use useCallback)
- Use FlatList not ScrollView for any list that could exceed 10 items
- Always handle loading, empty, and error states in screens

---

## Supabase Rules

- Initialise client once in `/lib/supabase.ts`
- All database calls go through service functions in `/lib/` — never call Supabase directly from a component
- Always handle errors explicitly — never assume a query succeeded
- Use Row Level Security (RLS) on all tables — users can only access their own data

---

## Offline Rules

Habit logging must work offline. Use a local queue (AsyncStorage or MMKV) that syncs to Supabase when connectivity is restored. Never block the user from marking a habit because of a network issue.

---

## RevenueCat Rules

- Initialise in app startup, before any screen renders
- Product identifier: `momentum_annual` (annual subscription)
- Entitlement identifier: `premium`
- Trial: 30 days, configured in App Store Connect and Google Play Console
- Always check entitlement status on app foreground, not just on launch
- Post-trial state: user can read history but cannot log new habits

---

## What NOT to Do

- Do not install unnecessary packages — ask before adding any new dependency
- Do not use class components — functional components and hooks only
- Do not put business logic in components — keep components presentational
- Do not use `console.log` in production code — use a proper logger or remove
- Do not hardcode user IDs, habit IDs, or any test data in production code
- Do not create files outside the structure above without flagging it first
